  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in the vast majority of jurisdictions around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (from activities such as drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other criminal acts) appear legitimate by passing it through a series of transactions or businesses. This practice is illegal because it enables criminal activity to continue and undermines the integrity of financial systems.\n\nGovernments and international organizations, such as the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**, have established laws and regulations to combat money laundering. Many countries have enacted specific legislation to criminalize money laundering and require financial institutions to implement measures to detect, prevent, and report suspicious activities. Penalties for money laundering can include significant fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
